article.headline: South Dakota State 79, UMKC 71 (OT)
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Kai Williams scored seven of his 17 points in overtime to help South Dakota State to a 79-71 win over Missouri-Kansas City on Tuesday. Williams started the scoring in overtime with a 3-point shot 32 seconds into the extra period, then added two free throws and a dunk off a turnover. Garrett Callahan was 8-of-8 from the free-throw line in overtime and 11-of-12 for the game. The victory broke a three-game losing streak for the Jackrabbits (3-10). The Kangaroos (4-9) led 36-31 at halftime, but could not shake South Dakota State. South Dakota State was led by Blake Yackley with 18 points. Four other Jackrabbits scored in double figures, led by Williams with 17, Jose Frias and Callahan with 16 each and Matt Cadwell with 12. Dee Ayuba came off the bench to lead the Kangaroos with 16 points and Brent Stephens added 15. Quinton Day, who came into the game leading the Mid-Continent Conference in scoring with a 21.2 average, had a season-low eight points. He was 3-of-11 from the floor and just 2-of-8 from 3-point range.
